# Remote Systems Configuration for opencode-sshfs
# ================================================
#
# Format: REMOTE_NAME|SSH_USER|SSH_HOST|REMOTE_PATH|LOCAL_MOUNT
#
# Field Descriptions:
#   REMOTE_NAME : Short identifier (alphanumeric, underscore, dash only)
#   SSH_USER    : Your username on the remote system
#   SSH_HOST    : Hostname or IP address (can match an SSH config Host entry)
#   REMOTE_PATH : Absolute path on remote (use $USER for your username if needed)
#   LOCAL_MOUNT : Local mount point (~ expands to your home directory)
#
# Notes:
#   - Lines starting with # are comments
#   - Each remote should be on its own line
#   - Do not use spaces around the | delimiter
#   - The LOCAL_MOUNT directory will be created automatically if it doesn't exist
#
# ============================================================================
# EXAMPLES - Uncomment and modify as needed
# ============================================================================

# HPC Clusters
# ------------
# curc|jdoe|login.rc.colorado.edu|/projects/jdoe/work|~/mounts/curc
# ncar_casper|jdoe|casper.hpc.ucar.edu|/glade/work/jdoe|~/mounts/casper
# ncar_derecho|jdoe|derecho.hpc.ucar.edu|/glade/derecho/scratch/jdoe|~/mounts/derecho

# University/Lab Servers
# ----------------------
# lab_server|researcher|lab.university.edu|/data/$USER/experiments|~/mounts/lab
# dept_compute|jdoe|compute.dept.edu|/home/$USER/projects|~/mounts/dept

# Cloud/VPS
# ---------
# aws_dev|ubuntu|ec2-xx-xx-xx-xx.compute.amazonaws.com|/home/ubuntu/app|~/mounts/aws
# digitalocean|root|123.45.67.89|/var/www|~/mounts/do

# Personal/Home
# -------------
# home_server|pi|192.168.1.100|/home/pi/projects|~/mounts/homeserver
# nas|admin|nas.local|/volume1/projects|~/mounts/nas

